  "doc_id": "23663",
  "text": "In Poland JW declare that, from their point of view, education is necessary. At the same time they emphasize the importance of \"a balanced view of education\", assuming that spiritual education is more valuable than secular, because only Biblebased spiritual education is a source of life-saving knowledge about God. JW also believe that the Rollins, Gohel and other authors emphasize the necessity of careful documentation of the patient's declarations in the history [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Kidson-Gerber et al. recommend documenting the patient's decision according to the regulations of a given country and standards of a particular medical centre [CITATION_4] . As Gyamfi et al. point out, an important part of collected medical documentation is inclusion of the patient's last will and appointment of guardians for children in case of death [CITATION_5] .",
